<TEXT>This truck rides and handles well enough that even the wife doesn't mind driving it. It's comfortable for my 6-2 large frame even on a 300 mile straight through drive (which is the freeway distance you will go between fill-ups). Fit and finish is outstanding. Treat it gently as the sheet metal is paper thin and dents can accumulate very easily. The same applies to the paint job (paper thin). Have had the truck for a year and a half and have had no warranty issues whatsoever. This won't replace a Ford F250, but you'd be better off buying it over a F150. </TEXT>
<FAVORITE>Tilt wheel, decent sound system, bluetooth, tons of storage space, assisted tailgate, electric folding outside mirrors (great to have on the ferry), excellent headlamp system.</FAVORITE>
